---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-bofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/",
  "slug": "monthly-bookkeeping",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-bofu",
  "bodyClass": "page--bofu",
  "title": "Monthly Bookkeeping Services · TechBrot",
  "description": "Recurring monthly bookkeeping for U.S. small and mid-sized businesses — real reconciliations, full monthly close, financial package by the 15th. Fixed monthly fee, named Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor operator. We keep the books; your CPA files.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Accounting", "href": "/accounting/" },
    { "name": "Bookkeeping", "href": "/accounting/bookkeeping/" },
    { "name": "Monthly bookkeeping" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Monthly bookkeeping",
    "heading": "Books closed every month. By a real operator. On time.",
    "subheading": "Recurring monthly bookkeeping for U.S. small and mid-sized businesses &mdash; real reconciliations, a full monthly close, and a financial package by the 15th. Delivered by a named Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor you can actually reach. Fixed monthly fee, written scope, no hourly billing.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=monthly", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>Monthly bookkeeping</strong> is a recurring engagement where a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor closes your books every month &mdash; reconciling every account to actual statements, categorizing transactions, verifying payroll and sales tax, and delivering a monthly financial package (P&amp;L, balance sheet, cash flow) <strong>by the 15th</strong>. Fixed monthly fee, written scope, named operator.",
    "source": "Fixed-fee · all 50 states · we keep the books, your CPA files. Not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Monthly starts here",
    "heading": "Let&rsquo;s scope a monthly engagement.",
    "lede": "Book a free 30-minute discovery call. We&rsquo;ll review your file, scope the right tier, and tell you what monthly bookkeeping will cost &mdash; in writing &mdash; before any work begins. No pitch, no obligation.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=monthly", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact" id="monthly-bookkeeping-proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="proof-strip">
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>4&times;</b> Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Monthly</b> close on schedule</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Fixed-fee</b> written scope, first</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>1 business day</b> response</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><span class="proof-strip__rating">5.0</span> 2 verified Clutch reviews</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="monthly-bookkeeping-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What monthly bookkeeping is.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Monthly bookkeeping is a recurring engagement where a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor closes the books every month &mdash; reconciling bank and credit card accounts against actual statements, categorizing transactions, verifying payroll and sales tax entries, and delivering a monthly financial package: P&amp;L, balance sheet, and cash flow statement. The close package arrives <strong>by the 15th of the following month</strong>.</p>
      <p>Monthly engagements start from a known-current state, so businesses with a backlog typically begin with <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/catch-up-bookkeeping/?intent=catch-up">catch-up bookkeeping</a> first, and businesses with messy books begin with <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup">cleanup bookkeeping</a> first &mdash; then transition seamlessly to monthly with the same operator.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="monthly-bookkeeping-cadence">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The monthly close cadence</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What every month actually looks like.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement runs the same close cadence &mdash; documents in, reconciliation, close and review, package delivered by the 15th.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for step in closeCadence %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ step.band | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ step.label | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ step.sub | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="monthly-bookkeeping-deliverables">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The deliverables</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What you get, every month.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h3>Included in every engagement</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for d in included %}<li>{{ d | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Layered on as scope requires</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for d in layered %}<li>{{ d | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="monthly-bookkeeping-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Monthly bookkeeping, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="monthly-bookkeeping-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Is it time?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="monthly-bookkeeping-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed monthly fee, written scope, no hourly billing.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Three tiers, each a fixed monthly fee against a written scope. Final pricing follows the diagnostic; most engagements include a one-time onboarding fee. See the <a href="/pricing/?intent=pricing">bookkeeping pricing page</a> for full detail.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        {%- if t.note %}<p class="review-card__role">{{ t.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.price | safe }}</strong>{{ t.per | safe }}</p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>For:</strong> {{ t.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in t.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/contact/?intent=monthly">{{ t.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="monthly-bookkeeping-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who performs the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A named, credentialed local operator.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot monthly engagement is delivered by a vetted local operator &mdash; an independent accounting practice running under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, standards, and infrastructure. You&rsquo;ll know exactly who is closing your books and how to reach them. Platform-level quality review backs every monthly close, and if continuity is ever a question, the platform handles the transition without losing file context. You&rsquo;re never stuck with one bookkeeper.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="monthly-bookkeeping-next">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before or after monthly</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Monthly is often the destination after another engagement.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in nextSteps %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="monthly-bookkeeping-intake">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Start now</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Start monthly bookkeeping.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Tell us the basics and a Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day with a written fixed-fee scope. Prefer the full intake? The <a href="/contact/?intent=monthly">complete contact form</a> captures every detail.</p>
    </header>
    {%- set intakePrefix = "mb" %}
    {%- set intakeFormId = "monthly-bookkeeping-intake-form" %}
    {%- set intakeIntent = "monthly" %}
    {%- set intakeSourceType = "bofu-conversion" %}
    {%- set intakeFunnelStage = "BOFU" %}
    {%- set intakeLegend = "What we should look at" %}
    {%- set intakeNote = "Monthly bookkeeping is the common reason businesses reach this page &mdash; add anything else you want scoped in the same call." %}
    {%- set intakeConsent = "I agree to be contacted by TechBrot regarding this monthly bookkeeping inquiry." %}
    {%- set intakeSubmit = "Send the Discovery Brief" %}
    {%- set intakeReassurance = "No spam, no list, no obligation. A Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day." %}
    {% include "partials/intake-form.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="monthly-bookkeeping-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask before starting monthly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="monthly-bookkeeping-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="monthly-bookkeeping-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
